{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01NS4NUbeurdrEmNz7ooWjYx","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full picture:\n- Prometheus runs on port 9090 internally, but the Service maps port 8000 to 9090 (the service exposes 8000/TCP)\n- The Prometheus config only scrapes itself at `localhost:9090`\n- RabbitMQ exposes metrics on port 15692 at `/metrics`\n- There are 3 RabbitMQ pods: rabbitmq-0, rabbitmq-1, rabbitmq-2\n- There's a headless service `rabbitmq-headless` with port 15692\n\nThe fix is straightforward: update the `prometheus-config` ConfigMap to add a scrape job for RabbitMQ that targets each of the 3 pods via the headless service DNS names.\nThe headless service creates DNS entries for each pod, so I can target them directly at `rabbitmq-0.rabbitmq-headless:15692`, `rabbitmq-1.rabbitmq-headless:15692`, and `rabbitmq-2.rabbitmq-headless:15692`. Since Prometheus has the lifecycle API enabled, I can update the ConfigMap and then trigger a reload via a POST request to `/-/reload` rather than restarting the pod.\n\nBefore I add the scrape configuration though, I should verify that RabbitMQ's metrics endpoint is actually responding.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1527,"cache_read_input_tokens":31967,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1527},"output_tokens":20,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"38b1f76b-3b87-42c6-80c3-863de02750b8","uuid":"c33ff8d2-35ba-416a-9aa8-8f4f4ff917f6","request_id":"req_011CcMSjaNZaRorKc1tEeRhP"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01NS4NUbeurdrEmNz7ooWjYx","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The Prometheus container listens on 9090; the Service maps it to 8000. The config only scrapes itself. Let me verify the RabbitMQ metrics endpoint is reachable first, then patch the ConfigMap and reload:"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1527,"cache_read_input_tokens":31967,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1527},"output_tokens":20,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"38b1f76b-3b87-42c6-80c3-863de02750b8","uuid":"efbc41cb-277a-4c41-8975-fd1158070d43","request_id":"req_011CcMSjaNZaRorKc1tEeRhP"}
