{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_015RwNwCnw1uu9QNfcMothwm","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So Prometheus loaded config that only has 1 job (`prometheus`), not the rabbitmq job. Even though the file `/etc/prometheus/prometheus.yml` inside the pod shows the rabbitmq job!\n\nWait, that's contradictory. Let me re-check what's happening:\n\n1. I checked the config file inside the pod with `cat /etc/prometheus/prometheus.yml` and it showed the full config with rabbitmq targets.\n2. The Prometheus API `/api/v1/status/config` shows only the original config without rabbitmq.\n3. The Prometheus logs show it loaded the config file at 04:21:56.\n4. I think there might be a timing issue here - the ConfigMap could have been updated, but the reload request might have gone through before the mounted volume actually reflected those changes. ConfigMap volume mounts can have a delay of up to a couple minutes before the file updates in the pod, so I may have reloaded with the old config and then the file updated afterward.\n\nLet me send another reload request now that the file has actually been updated with the new configuration.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":694,"cache_read_input_tokens":39721,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":694},"output_tokens":20,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"38b1f76b-3b87-42c6-80c3-863de02750b8","uuid":"4181c73d-bad4-4335-95cb-529d9812c39e","request_id":"req_011CcMSrFhbc7XAig7uoaEQP"}
